body:
### Describe the bug

I work with the AWS IoT SDK to fetch information about my devices that are stored in AWS. On Quarkus version 2.16.7.Final everything works as expected. I create the client like this
`
private final IotClient iotClient;

    @Inject
    public DeviceCouplingIotService() {
        this.iotClient = IotClient.create();
    }

When I want to upgrade to a version higher than the version I use now, I cannot create the client like this. Other ways of creating the client, dont work either. The version of the AWS SDK doesn't matter. I've started on version `2.18.41` and could upgrade to `2.20.154` without any problems.

This problem only occurs when deploy to AWS Lambda. When testing locally, the code behaves like expected.

### Expected behavior

Return the information about the device that I'm requesting

### Actual behavior

